(nICacheTLBWays, power_internal).explanation: Increasing instruction cache TLB associativity requires additional comparison logic and storage structures, directly increasing internal power consumption of the TLB subsystem;

(nICacheTLBWays, area_net_area).explanation: Higher TLB associativity necessitates more complex interconnect routing between additional comparison units and storage elements, increasing the net area required for wiring;

(nICacheTLBWays, nDCacheTLBWays).explanation: Instruction cache TLB associativity and data cache TLB associativity are independent microarchitectural design parameters that can be configured separately;
